  Dialogue:
  - Warriors used to hate <color=yellow>Sarka</color>'s bards, <color=purple>William</color>
    only began to understand this hatred when he heard a terrible song about how
    criminals were smart.
  - About how the followers of the <color=yellow>law</color> were fools.
  - About how the criminals were happy.
  - About how the followers of the <color=yellow>law</color> were  sad.
  - About how criminals were free.
  - About how followers of the <color=yellow>law</color> were slaves.
  - The music made a bit of sense, a criminal was able to enjoy the perks of crime,
    while a follower of the <color=yellow>law</color> one was not. But everything
    that bard said in his song would be reversed the moment the criminal was caught.
  - <color=purple>William</color> figured that bard would learn this important lesson
    when he was arrested.
  DialogueBR:
  - "Guerreiros costumavam odiar os bardos de <color=yellow>Sarka</color>, <color=purple>William</color>
    s\xF3 come\xE7ou a entender esse \xF3dio quando ouviu uma m\xFAsica terr\xEDvel
    sobre como os criminosos eram inteligentes."
  - Sobre como os seguidores da <color=yellow>lei</color> eram tolos.
  - Sobre como os criminosos eram felizes.
  - Sobre como os seguidores da <color=yellow>lei</color> era tristes.
  - Sobre como os criminosos eram livres.
  - Sobre como os seguidores da <color=yellow>lei</color> eram escravos.
  - "A m\xFAsica fazia um pouco de sentido, um criminoso era capaz de aproveitar
    as vantagens do crime, enquanto um seguidor da <color=yellow>lei</color> n\xE3o.
    Mas tudo o que aquele bardo dizia em sua can\xE7\xE3o seria revertido no momento
    em que o criminoso fosse pego."
  - "<color=purple>William</color> imaginou que o bardo aprenderia essa importante
    li\xE7\xE3o quando fosse preso."
